      <section class="aboutbio">
        <section class="card bio">
          <img alt="" src="/assets/images/about/michele.png" />
          <section>
            <h2>Michele Tornetta</h2>
            <h3>Co-Founder of GoLive WebDev</h3>
            <h4>Web Developer &amp; Online Marketing Consultant</h4>
            <p>I enjoy developing user friendly interatcive websites and apps that define an organization or individual.
              It's my belief that every website should be unique and tell a story visually and through content.</p>
            <p>I have a background in online marketing and business development. It's my marketing experience that
              taught
              me that a website isn't enough, you need to have a have a sight that has a call to action. It's important
              to
              keep people's attention and to be very clear on what you want a customer to do while on your site or app.
            </p>
            <p>After coding simple websites and email templates, I chose to attend the University of Pennsylvania Coding
              Bootcamp, graduating in the top of my class.</p>
            <p>On a more personal note, my first passion is my family and I love to spend time outdoors riding horses,
              gardening, kayaking and hiking.</p>
          </section>
        </section>
        <section class="card bio">
          <img alt="" src="/assets/images/about/anthony.png" />
          <section>
            <h2>Anthony Tornetta</h2>
            <h3>Co-Founder of GoLive WebDev</h3>
            <h4>Full-Stack Software Engineer</h4>
            <p>From building enterprise-grade applications to simple homepages, I have experience in it all.
              I ensure that every website I make is hand-crafted with security being my first concern.
            </p>
            <p>I make it my number one priority that every customer always has a positive experience.
              Websites I build are tailored towards accessibility, so no customer should ever have trouble
              reading or interacting with your content.
            </p>
            <p>I make sure that your website will stand out against your competition, both through its speed,
              usability,
              accessibility, and visual pizzazz.</p>
          </section>
